	<H1 CLASS="start2">
Cicero: de Officiis
	</H1>


	<P CLASS="start2 a0 justify">
There are at least ten copies online of this edition of the <I>de Officiis</I>, in English translation. I put this one up because those ten copies, all apparently taken from a single scanned source, are very bad. Not just the inevitable typo here and there, but some twenty instances of multiple lines missing, usually the last two to six of the printed page; and two instances where three-quarters of a page had been skipped. (For detailed comments and an example of the nonsense that resulted on these clone sites, see
	<A HREF="
https://rambambashi.wordpress.com/2010/06/10/moral-duty/
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
"Moral duty"
	</A>
at <I>New at LacusCurtius and Livius</I>.)
	<P CLASS="i1 b0 a0 justify">
Since I'm not so interested in philosophy, reading the work once was enough for me, and I dispensed with retyping it from scratch. I lifted one of those abominable scans, then reformatted it, proofread it word for word against my own print copy of the book, keying in of course the missing passages; added the missing notes, corrected the chapter numbering, added the section numbers and pagination, cut it up into Web-manageable reader-friendly chunks, provided my usual local links down to the section level; added the editors' introduction and bibliography.

	<P CLASS="justify">
I'll probably also put the Latin onsite at some point, but not urgently: it's already online
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/cicero/off.shtml
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
at Latin Library</A>, and surely any typos there won't be as bad as those that made it my moral duty, as it were, to put the English onsite. Details on the technical aspects of the layout of my own site follow the Table of Contents.


